title: Generate Fibonacci Sequence

codeSnippets.code: /**  * @return {Generator<number>}  */ var fibGenerator = function*() {      };  /**  * const gen = fibGenerator();  * gen.next().value; // 0  * gen.next().value; // 1  */
function* fibGenerator(): Generator<number, any, number> {      };  /**  * const gen = fibGenerator();  * gen.next().value; // 0  * gen.next().value; // 1  */

content: Write a generator function that returns a generator object which yields thefibonacci sequence. Thefibonacci sequenceis defined by the relation Xn= Xn-1+ Xn-2. The first few numbersof the series are 0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13.  Example 1:  Input: callCount = 5 Output: [0,1,1,2,3] Explanation: const gen = fibGenerator(); gen.next().value; // 0 gen.next().value; // 1 gen.next().value; // 1 gen.next().value; // 2 gen.next().value; // 3  Example 2:  Input: callCount = 0 Output: [] Explanation: gen.next() is never called so nothing is outputted   Constraints:  0 <= callCount <= 50
